# File Organization and Project Structure

## Testnet Directory
- All non-project files MUST be in `testnet/` directory
- Includes: test configs, temporary files, test node data, test logs, experimental files
- Exceptions: Source code (`app/`, `cmd/`, `x/`, `proto/`), documentation (`docs/`), config files

## Documentation Organization
- Specifications go to `docs/`: architecture, API, protocols, system design, economic model, consensus, modules, infrastructure
- All other documentation goes to `deprecated/`: deployment guides, improvement plans, user guides, status reports
- Exception: `README.md` stays in root

## Documentation Naming
- Use UPPERCASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES.md format
- Examples: `PRODUCTION_DEPLOYMENT.md`, `DOCKER_DEPLOYMENT.md`
- Exception: `README.md` can use any case

## Infrastructure Directory
- All infrastructure files in `infrastructure/`: Docker scripts, monitoring configs, Grafana dashboards
- Structure: `infrastructure/docker/`, `infrastructure/monitoring/`, `infrastructure/grafana/`
- Referenced in `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml`

## Backend Directory
- All backend services and API servers go to `backend/`: REST API servers, gRPC gateways, microservices, background workers
- Structure: `backend/api/`, `backend/services/`, `backend/workers/`, `backend/utils/`
- Backend services are separate from blockchain node (`cmd/volnixd/`) and application code (`app/`)
- Examples: REST API wrapper, webhook services, indexing services, external API integrations
- Each service should have its own subdirectory with `README.md` and configuration files

## Non-Source Files (MUST be in .gitignore)
- Check `.gitignore` BEFORE creating non-source files
- If pattern exists → safe to create, if not → add to `.gitignore` first
- Non-source categories:
  - Build artifacts: `build/`, `frontend/*/build/`, `*.exe`, `*.o`, `*.test`, `coverage/`
  - Generated code: `proto/gen/`, `.generated/`
  - Dependencies: `vendor/`, `node_modules/`, lock files
  - Test data: `testnet/`, `tmp/`, `*.log`, `*.bak`
  - Local config: `.volnix/`, `.env`, `config.toml`, `*.db`, private keys
  - IDE/OS files: `.vscode/`, `.DS_Store`, `*.swp`
  - Deprecated: `deprecated/`

## Project Structure
- Root: essential project files only
- Source code: `app/`, `cmd/`, `x/`, `proto/volnix/`, `tests/`
- Backend services: `backend/` (committed, separate services from blockchain node)
- Config/scripts: `config/`, `scripts/`, `docs/`, `.cursor/`
- Infrastructure: `infrastructure/` (committed, required for deployment)
- Test artifacts: `testnet/` (ignored)
- Build artifacts: `build/`, `proto/gen/` (ignored)

## .gitignore Rules
- All non-source patterns MUST be in `.gitignore` before creation
- Update both this file and `.gitignore` when adding new patterns
- Files in `.gitignore` = safe to create, files NOT in `.gitignore` = will be committed

## Best Practices
- Always check `.gitignore` before creating non-source files
- Never create non-source files not in `.gitignore`
- Keep this file and `.gitignore` synchronized
- Organize testnet files by purpose (e.g., `testnet/node0/`)
- Clean up testnet directory periodically
